vec3 pdC(vec3 a,vec3 b,float c,float d,vec4 m,float f){return mix(a,b,m.w)*f*c*d+b*m.z*(1.-c)+a*m.y*(1.-d);}//many contextual simplifications possible.
#define pdA(c,d,m)suv(m*vec3(c*d,c*(1.-d),d*(1.-c)))
//#define pdA(c,d,m)m.x*c*d+m.y*c*(1.-d)+m.z*d*(1.-c)
//xor case is simpler,likely worth making it a subroutine of pdC;
//#define pdCx(a,b,c,d,m)m.y*a*(1.-d)+m.z*b*(1.-c)
//vec3 pdCx(vec3 a,vec3 b,float c,float d){return a*d+b*c;}
vec4 pd(vec4 a,vec4 b,vec4 m,float f){
 vec4 r=vec4(pdC(a.rgb,b.rgb,a.w,b.w,m,f),1);//ceneral case color
 r.w=pdA(a.w,b.w,m.rgb);//general case alpha is sometimes neglible.
 return r;}
//return a*a.w+b*b.w*(1.-a.w);//general case reduction shortcut
vec4 sOver(vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(1,1,1,0),1.);}
vec4 sAtop(vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(1,0,1,0),1.);}
vec4 sIn (vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(1,0,0,1),1.);}
vec4 sXor(vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(0,1,1,1),0.);}
vec4 sOut(vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(0,0,1,0),0.);}
vec4 sCut(vec4 a,vec4 b){return pd(a,b,vec4(0,0,1,1),0.);}




